The paper proposes a model for representation learning of knowledge bases, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The model also addresses relation extraction from text, which falls under natural language processing (cs.CL). The use of low-dimensional embeddings for representation learning is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also deals with the reliability of relation paths, which is a challenge in database management (cs.DB). Finally, the paper involves semantic composition of relation embeddings, which is a technique used in information retrieval (cs.IR).
